### Passing React Hooks: Avoid Dynamic Usage and Prop Passing in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/rules/react-calls-components-and-hooks.md

Hooks should not be passed around dynamically, for example, as props to components. This practice complicates debugging, reduces local reasoning, and can lead to violations of the Rules of Hooks. Always call Hooks directly within the component or Hook where their functionality is needed.

```javascript
function ChatInput() {
  return <Button useData={useDataWithLogging} /> // üî¥ Bad: don't pass Hooks as props
}
```

```javascript
function ChatInput() {
  return <Button />
}

function Button() {
  const data = useDataWithLogging(); // ‚úÖ Good: Use the Hook directly
}

function useDataWithLogging() {
  // If there's any conditional logic to change the Hook's behavior, it should be inlined into
  // the Hook
}
```

