### Identify invalid React component and hook factories in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/eslint-plugin-react-hooks/lints/component-hook-factories.md

This code snippet demonstrates examples of invalid patterns where React components or custom hooks are defined inside other functions, leading to re-creation on every render, state loss, and performance issues. This includes factory functions creating components, components defined within other components, and hook factory functions.

```javascript
// ‚ùå Factory function creating components
function createComponent(defaultValue) {
  return function Component() {
    // ...
  };
}

// ‚ùå Component defined inside component
function Parent() {
  function Child() {
    // ...
  }

  return <Child />;
}

// ‚ùå Hook factory function
function createCustomHook(endpoint) {
  return function useData() {
    // ...
  };
}
```

