### Correct Usage of React Hooks in Function Components and Custom Hooks

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/warnings/invalid-hook-call-warning.md

This example demonstrates the correct placement for calling React Hooks, such as `useState`. Hooks must be called at the top level of a function component or a custom Hook, ensuring they are not nested within conditions, loops, or other functions.

```javascript
function Counter() {
  // ‚úÖ Good: top-level in a function component
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  // ...
}

function useWindowWidth() {
  // ‚úÖ Good: top-level in a custom Hook
  const [width, setWidth] = useState(window.innerWidth);
  // ...
}
```

