### React `use` API for Chained Data Fetching

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md

This example illustrates a potential future pattern for data fetching within a React functional component using the `use` hook. It shows how to perform chained data fetches, where the result of one `fetch` call (`cities`) is used to inform a subsequent `fetch` call (`areas`), demonstrating a declarative approach to asynchronous operations.

```js
import { use } from 'react';

function ShippingForm({ country }) {
  const cities = use(fetch(`/api/cities?country=${country}`));
  const [city, setCity] = useState(null);
  const areas = city ? use(fetch(`/api/areas?city=${city}`)) : null;
  // ...
```

