### Avoid Custom 'Lifecycle' Hooks (e.g., useMount) in React Components

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md

Illustrates an anti-pattern: using a custom `useMount` hook that wraps `useEffect`. This approach leads to issues like overlooked dependencies and bypasses React linter checks, making debugging harder. It discourages custom Hooks that merely abstract `useEffect` lifecycle.

```js
function ChatRoom({ roomId }) {
  const [serverUrl, setServerUrl] = useState('https://localhost:1234');

  // üî¥ Avoid: using custom "lifecycle" Hooks
  useMount(() => {
    const connection = createConnection({ roomId, serverUrl });
    connection.connect();

    post('/analytics/event', { eventName: 'visit_chat' });
  });
  // ...
}

// üî¥ Avoid: creating custom "lifecycle" Hooks
function useMount(fn) {
  useEffect(() => {
    fn();
  }, []); // üî¥ React Hook useEffect has a missing dependency: 'fn'
}
```

