### Optimizing Custom React Hook Returned Functions with useCallback

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/react/useCallback.md

When creating custom React Hooks, it's good practice to wrap any functions returned by the hook (e.g., `navigate`, `goBack`) with `useCallback`. This optimization ensures that consumers of the hook receive stable function references, allowing them to effectively memoize or optimize their own components that use these functions.

```javascript
function useRouter() {
  const { dispatch } = useContext(RouterStateContext);

  const navigate = useCallback((url) => {
    dispatch({ type: 'navigate', url });
  }, [dispatch]);

  const goBack = useCallback(() => {
    dispatch({ type: 'back' });
  }, [dispatch]);

  return {
    navigate,
    goBack,
  };
}
```

