### Avoid Mutating Hook Arguments Directly (Bad Example)

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/rules/components-and-hooks-must-be-pure.md

Demonstrates an incorrect practice of directly modifying an object passed as an argument to a custom React Hook. Mutating hook arguments can lead to unpredictable behavior and break memoization optimizations within the hook, violating the immutability principle.

```js
function useIconStyle(icon) {
  const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);
  if (icon.enabled) {
    icon.className = computeStyle(icon, theme); // ‚ìâ Bad: never mutate hook arguments directly
  }
  return icon;
}
```

