### Implement useCounter Custom Hook and Refactor Counter Component (React)

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md

This solution extracts the counter logic into a `useCounter` custom Hook, making the `Counter` component cleaner and reusable. The `useCounter` Hook encapsulates the `useState` and `useEffect` logic, returning the current count.

```javascript
import { useCounter } from './useCounter.js';

export default function Counter() {
  const count = useCounter();
  return <h1>Seconds passed: {count}</h1>;
}
```

```javascript
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export function useCounter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  useEffect(() => {
    const id = setInterval(() => {
      setCount(c => c + 1);
    }, 1000);
    return () => clearInterval(id);
  }, []);
  return count;
}
```

