### Implement dynamic React components by passing JSX as children in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/eslint-plugin-react-hooks/lints/component-hook-factories.md

This code snippet demonstrates the correct way to achieve dynamic component behavior in React by passing JSX as children. This approach avoids factory functions, ensuring component stability, preserving state, and maintaining good performance. It's the recommended pattern for flexible component rendering.

```javascript
// ‚úÖ Better: Pass JSX as children
function Button({color, children}) {
  return (
    <button style={{backgroundColor: color}}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}

function App() {
  return (
    <>
      <Button color="red">Red</Button>
      <Button color="blue">Blue</Button>
    </>
  );
}
```

