### Integrate `useList` custom Hook into a React component

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/react/cloneElement.md

This `App` component demonstrates how to consume the `useList` custom Hook. It destructures `selected` and `onNext` from the hook, rendering a list of products and a button to navigate through them, highlighting the currently selected item based on the hook's state.

```javascript
export default function App() {
  const [selected, onNext] = useList(products);
  return (
    <div className="List">
      {products.map(product =>
        <Row
          key={product.id}
          title={product.title}
          isHighlighted={selected === product}
        />
      )}
      <hr />
      <button onClick={onNext}>
        Next
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

