### Render React Component with Custom useFadeIn Hook

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md

This React JavaScript code defines an `App` component that controls the visibility of a `Welcome` component using `useState`. The `Welcome` component then utilizes a custom `useFadeIn` hook with `useRef` to apply a fade-in animation to an `h1` element when rendered, demonstrating imperative animation logic encapsulated in a hook.

```js
import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';
import { useFadeIn } from './useFadeIn.js';

function Welcome() {
  const ref = useRef(null);

  useFadeIn(ref, 1000);

  return (
    <h1 className="welcome" ref={ref}>
      Welcome
    </h1>
  );
}

export default function App() {
  const [show, setShow] = useState(false);
  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => setShow(!show)}>
        {show ? 'Remove' : 'Show'}
      </button>
      <hr />
      {show && <Welcome />}
    </>
  );
}
```

