### React useData Custom Hook for Centralized Data Fetching

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md

This custom React hook encapsulates the common data fetching logic from the `ShippingForm` component. It takes a URL as input and returns the fetched data, abstracting `useState` and `useEffect` to provide a cleaner API for components.

```js
function useData(url) {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);
  useEffect(() => {
    if (url) {
      let ignore = false;
      fetch(url)
        .then(response => response.json())
        .then(json => {
          if (!ignore) {
            setData(json);
          }
        });
      return () => {
        ignore = true;
      };
    }
  }, [url]);
  return data;
}
```

